answer: Non-GAAP operating margin decreased. Other operating (income) expense, net, as a distinct line item, was reflected within the operating income components. A reduction of $147.5 million in operating income from $147.5 million in 2023 to $5,844 million in 2024 corresponded to the $5,844 million (Non-GAAP operating income) decrease, which contributed to the decrease in Non-GAAP operating margin. Specifically, operating income in 2023 was $147.5 million, and in 2024, $5,844 million (Non-GAAP operating income) was reflected in the 2024 10-K. The difference in operating income directly accounts for the change in non-GAAP operating margin. (Operating Income in 2023: $147.5 million, Operating Income in 2024: $5,844 million)
